Funds for:
Expenditures on assistance (Ln.5) basic assistance, and;
Subsidized on non-assistance (Ln.6) 6.A_1work-related activities and expenses, and 6.H prev. out-of-wedlock pregnancy.

This payment request is submitted as a replacement drawdown for the Z27 transaction dated 04/19/25, which was previously approved by the Grants Management Specialist (GMS). The original payment check was misrouted within the internal university mailing system and was not retrieved in a timely manner. As a result, it could not be processed or deposited within the required timeframe. To ensure proper accounting and program continuity, a replacement payment is necessary.

The requested funds will reimburse the University of Southern California (USC) for allowable and allocable expenses incurred under the Head Start grant through 10/31/2024. These include:

•	Personnel salaries and wages for staff providing Head Start services during the covered period;
•	Fringe benefits and indirect costs, calculated in accordance with the approved cost allocation plan;
•	Operational costs such as instructional supplies, child nutrition services, and program equipment;
•	Facility and occupancy expenses proportionate to program delivery.


These expenditures were incurred in alignment with the approved scope and budget of the grant award. This replacement payment is being issued solely to address the administrative issue of the delayed check retrieval and does not represent any new or unapproved expenditures.

This explanation is provided in accordance with Executive Order 14222, which underscores the importance of financial transparency and alignment of federal funds with their authorized purposes.

